CHARTS

Which Electric Vehicle to Choose

Scatter Voronoi

Photo by Michael Marais on Unsplash

Economic growth doesn’t mean anything if it leaves people out…
— Jack Kemp

Load the data [Ingest]

# Load data
url_root <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/UN-AVT/kamino-source/main/sources/0-shared/data/"
url_file <- "which-electric-vehicle-to-choose/Cheapestelectriccars-EVDatabase.csv"
url <- paste0(url_root, url_file)

df <- read.csv(url, header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
df

Prepare the data [Wrangle]

While creating a heatmap, it might make better sense to bin the continuous data into levels and represent each level as a discrete colour. The cut() function in R allows to break and label a continuous variable

df$Acceleration <- parse_number(df$Acceleration)
df$TopSpeed <- parse_number(df$TopSpeed)
df$Range <- parse_number(df$Range)
df$Price.UK <- parse_number(df$Price.UK)

df$Name <- sub("(\\w+\\s+\\w+).*", "\\1", df$Name)

df <- df %>%  mutate(zero2sixty=cut(Acceleration, breaks=c(0,4,6,8,10,12),
                      labels=c('3-4','4-6','6-8','8-10','12+'))) %>%
  mutate(zero2sixty = as.factor(zero2sixty))

Plot

Top Speed and Price

theme_opts <- theme(
    text = element_text(family = "inconsolata"), 
    plot.title = element_text(color = "green", size = 14, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(color = "black", size = 12),
    plot.caption = element_text(color = "#555555", size = 8),
    axis.text = element_text(size=7.5),
    panel.border = element_blank(),
    panel.background = element_blank(),
    legend.title = element_text(color = "black", size = 8, face = "bold"), # remove legend title
    legend.text = element_text(color = "black", size = 8),
    legend.position='right'
)


v1 <- ggplot(data = df, aes(y= TopSpeed,
                      x= rescale(Price.UK, to=c(135,250)),
                      label = Name))+
  stat_voronoi(geom="path", colour = 'green') +
  geom_point(aes(color=zero2sixty)) +
  geom_text_repel(size=4, aes(color=zero2sixty)) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(140, 160, 200, 240),
                  labels=c(10000, 20000,30000, 64111)) +
      labs(y="Top Speed",
           x = "Price",
       title = "Which EV to Choose?",
       subtitle = "Pinpoint your desired Top Speed and Price",
       caption = "refer to data frame for full car name")+
  theme_opts

girafe(ggobj = v1, width_svg = 16, height_svg = 9,
       options = list(opts_sizing(rescale = TRUE, width = 0.8)))

Plot

Range and Price

v2 <- ggplot(data = df, aes(y= Range,
                      x= rescale(Price.UK, to=c(200,640)),
                      label = Name))+
  stat_voronoi(geom="path", colour = 'green') +
  geom_point(aes(color=zero2sixty)) +
  geom_text_repel(size=4, aes(color=zero2sixty))+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(200, 300, 400, 500, 600),
                  labels=c(30000, 45000,65000, 85000, 105000)) +
   labs(y="Range",
        x = "Price",
       title = "Which EV to Choose?",
       subtitle = "Pinpoint your desired Range and Price",
       caption = "refer to data frame for full car name") +
  theme_opts

girafe(ggobj = v2, width_svg = 16, height_svg = 9,
       options = list(opts_sizing(rescale = TRUE, width = 0.8)))
